15 subsections (3), (4), or (5) of this section shall be charged with a violation and
16 each violation shall constitute a separate offense.
17 (7) A violation of subsections (3), (4), or (5) of this section shall be deemed a status
18 offense if committed by a person under the age of eighteen (18) and shall be
19 under the jurisdiction of the juvenile session of the District Court or the family
20 division of the Circuit Court, as appropriate.
21 (8) It shall be an affirmative defense to a charge under subsection (2) of this section
22 that the sale was induced by the use of false, fraudulent, or altered identification
