9 SECTION 11. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 239 IS CREATED TO
10 READ AS FOLLOWS:
11 (1) There is hereby created a trust and agency account to be known as the Kentucky
12 hemp fund. The fund shall be administered by the Department of Psychoactive
13 Substances.
14 (2) For tax periods beginning on or after January 1, 2027, one hundred percent
15 (100%) of the receipts collected under this section from any state retail regulatory
16 license fee and state wholesale regulatory license fee from the sale of hemp
17 products regulated by this chapter shall be deposited in the fund together with
18 any other money contributed, appropriated, or allocated to the fund from all
19 other sources. The fund may also receive additional state appropriations, gifts,
20 grants, and federal funds. Notwithstanding KRS 45.229, any money remaining in
21 the fund at the close of any calendar year shall not lapse but shall be carried
22 forward to the next calendar year.
23 (3) (a) The Department of Psychoactive Substances shall use moneys deposited in
24 the Kentucky hemp fund to administer the fund and provide rewards for the
25 industry to be divided as follows:
26 1. At least ninety percent (90%) shall be allocated to regulating,
27 researching, and promoting Kentucky’s hemp industry. The funds
Page 26 of 146
XXXX 3/4/2026 12:01 PM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1643
1 shall be allocated as follows:
2 a. One percent (1%) shall be allocated to:
3 i. Fund cannabis education, which shall be used to deter
4 underage consumption;
5 ii. Provide educational materials for adults to support the
6 prevention of underage consumption; and
7 iii. Establish a safe consumption training program for retailers
8 participating in on-premises sales;
9 b. Up to five percent (5%) shall be allocated to the Department for
10 Public Health’s laboratory to upgrade facilities for testing
11 cannabis;
12 c. Up to five percent (5%) shall be allocated to the Kentucky State
13 Police to establish a field sobriety test for cannabis;
14 d. Up to four percent (4%) shall be allocated to administer and
15 regulate hemp products, including maintaining state laboratory
16 cannabinoid testing facilities using fit-for-purpose
17 methodologies;
18 e. At least eighty percent (80%) shall be allocated to the University
19 of Kentucky Cannabis Center to advance the study of cannabis.
20 Of this money, at least eighty-five percent (85%) of the funds
21 allocated under this subdivision shall exclusively be allocated to
22 advance hemp feed animal trials for livestock and companion
23 animals until the department determines that funding is no
24 longer required for the hemp animal feed approval process, and
25 up to fifteen percent (15%) shall be allocated to the other
26 purposes of this subdivision. Once this hemp animal feed
27 funding is no longer required, all funding under this subdivision
